            "open_state_collapse_bg": "#6d388b",
            "open_state_content_bg": "#fefaff",
            "open_state_content_text": "#121212",
            "content": "<p>Step 1: Place the board on a flat, stable surface<br/>Step 2: Let your child step on with one foot and stretch their arms out for balance<br/>Step 3: Switch feet, count seconds, or turn it into a fun challenge</p><p>Play ideas: obstacle courses, movement stations, balance contests, and imaginative play. Adult supervision is recommended for younger children.</p>",
